DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,9,1);
$b = random(1,9,1);

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Solve for \(x\): 
\( $a^x = e^{x+$b} \)

$PAR
\(x = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(Compute( "$b/(ln($a)-1)" )->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Taking the logarithm of both sides, we get
\[
  \ln($a^x) = \ln(e^{x+$b}),\quad\mbox{or}\quad
  x\ln($a) = (x+$b)\ln(e) = (x+$b).
\]
Thus
\[
 x(\ln($a) - 1) = $b,\quad\mbox{so}\quad
 x = \frac{$b}{\ln($a) - 1}.
\]
 
END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


